<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 9:43PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Armstrong and northwestern Donley Counties through 1015 PM CDT...
At 943 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Goodnight, or 11 miles east of Claude, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Goodnight.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
